Constant slowdowns really make things easier, it is a solid fact, with examples given in this thread - bullet hell shooters and TAS rely on this a lot. TAS in particular pushes this to extreme, with going to every next frame by pressing a special button.<br /><br />Random jumpy slowdowns could make things more difficult, no doubts here too.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Mon Nov 21, 2011 10:32 am</p><hr />
